We don't know.

55
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:52,440
鲁丝 晚上你一个人 待在这下面时 有没有想过
- You ever think, Ruth, all alone down here at night,

56
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:54,900
既然当初是雷顿抛下了我们
that since Layton bailed on us in the first place,

57
00:03:54,980 --> 00:03:56,570
他可能永远都不会回来了 
he might never come back?

58
00:03:58,110 --> 00:03:59,820
没想过
No, I don't.

59
00:04:00,610 --> 00:04:03,910
你也没有 否则你不会加入抵抗军
And neither do you, or you wouldn't be in the resistance.

60
00:04:03,990 --> 00:04:08,450
好了 这些抗生素给裁缝们 她们会需要的
- So antibiotics for the seamstresses. They'll need them,

61
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:10,750
大家都挤在那个血汗工厂里
all jammed up together in that sweatshop.

62
00:04:10,830 --> 00:04:13,290
这些小小的补给品能让我们保持理智
It's these little things that will keep us sane, Mr. Pike.

63
00:04:13,380 --> 00:04:16,300
如果我们能让旅途稍微舒服点 乘客们就能熬过这一关
The passengers can survive all of this if we can ease their journey.

64
00:04:17,510 --> 00:04:19,550
让他们为雷顿先生的归来做好准备
And keep them ready for Mr. Layton's return.

65
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:25,680
威尔福德1023节车厢长的集中营 轰隆前行
- The heart of hope still beats aboard Wilford's rolling gulag,

66
00:04:26,430 --> 00:04:28,980
在车上依然跳动着满怀希望的心
1,023 cars long.

67
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:08,100
好 这里应该不会有轨道污染物了
Okay. Should be clear of track contaminants.

68
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,680
我要开始采集冰样了
I'm gonna start pulling ice samples.

69
00:05:11,270 --> 00:05:12,440
外面看上去怎么样 
How's it looking?

70
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:14,650
棕榈树 金沙滩
- Palm trees, golden sands.

71
00:05:14,730 --> 00:05:17,110
我得去赶朝鲜的海浪
Gotta catch me some North Korean waves.

72
00:05:17,190 --> 00:05:19,440
真不错 我去拿一下冲浪板 马上就出去 兄弟
- Nice. I'll grab my board. I'll be right out, bro.

73
00:05:19,530 --> 00:05:20,360
